        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Either argument can be used to generalize to a corresponding n x n determinant, called a Moore determinant; we leave the precise formulation to the reader. Note the similarity with the classical Vandermonde determinant: if A is the n X n matrix with Aij = x for i, j=0,...,n - 1, then",
