      {
        "id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2002_Solutions_2002s_page_004_10",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Since both sides are homogeneous as polynomials in x and y, it suffices to check (4) for x = 1, as a congruence between polynomials. Now note that the right side has 0,1,...,P - 1 as roots modulo p, as does the left side. Moreover, both sides have the same leading coefficient. Since they both have degree only p, they must then coincide.",
        "bbox": [
          0.12593985717039372,
          0.5290178569800611,
          0.49060151109241035,
          0.6266909044538275
        ],
        "order": 15
